relevant_findings.description: Document details the CIA's 201 filing system for tracking individuals of interest
relevant_findings.direct_quote: The 201 system provides a means for identifying subjects of 201 files from various categories of information about them and for producing lists of 201 personalities according to those categories.
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals internal CIA documentation and tracking methodology for persons of interest, potentially relevant to understanding how Oswald might have been monitored

relevant_findings.description: System for maintaining detailed personal dossiers on individuals
relevant_findings.direct_quote: The 201 Dossier: the official file containing the 201 opening form and all biographical reporting on and references to the individual
relevant_findings.significance: Indicates systematic approach to collecting and maintaining comprehensive files on subjects, suggesting potential extensive background tracking

relevant_findings.description: Secret CIA Clandestine Services Handbook on Personality Indexing
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals internal CIA documentation practices for tracking personnel and operations

relevant_findings.description: Systematic approach to tracking personalities and assigning identification numbers
relevant_findings.direct_quote: A relatively small proportion of the total number of personalities indexed by the CS are of active operational interest at any given point in time.
relevant_findings.significance: Demonstrates CIA's systematic method for tracking and categorizing individuals of interest

relevant_findings.description: Strict protocols for concealing identities in intelligence files
relevant_findings.direct_quote: The 201 machine listings should include the identities of persons of operational interest because of their connection with a target group or organization
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals internal guidelines for maintaining operational secrecy while tracking individuals
